- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper deals with multi-agent systems and control algorithms. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper proposes a strategy for estimating velocity and position of agents in a system. 
- cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) is another possible category as the paper deals with controlling the formation shape and velocity consensus of agents in a multi-agent system. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper proposes an estimation method for agents executing arbitrary motions. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not explicitly deal with image or video data, but the proposed method could potentially be applied in computer vision applications.
